sql:
SELECT model_id
FROM model_sharing
WHERE share_type = 'public';

SELECT AVG(rating) AS average_rating
FROM model_ratings
WHERE researcher_id = (SELECT researcher_id FROM researchers WHERE name = 'Alice Johnson');

SELECT name
FROM models
ORDER BY created_at DESC;

external_knowledge:
- Average rating above 4.0 implies high-quality models; 
- Publicly shared models are those accessible to everyone;
- Performance metrics are used to evaluate the quality of models.

